1 August 2016The National Joint Operational and Intelligence Structure (NATJOINTS) will on Monday, 01 August 2016 brief media on the state of readiness by the South African security agencies to secure 2016 Local Government Elections. The briefing will take place in Vuwani, Limpopo.The Chairperson of the JCPS Cluster Directors-General, Dr Sam Gulube and the Acting National Commissioner Kgomotso Phahlane will do an assessment of the preparations ahead of the election. Among the sites to be visited is a high-tech National Joint Operations Centre in the area.Members of the media are invited. The media briefing will take place as follows:Date: Today, 01 August 2016 Time:10h00 Venue: Vuwani Police Station, Vuwani, Limpopo RSVP: Contact Pheliswa Sebati on 082 413 4609 Email: pheliswa@gcis.gov.za or Thanyani Ravhura on 082 421 3461 Email: thanyani@gcis.gov.za Enquiries: Siphiwe Dlamini 0836454294 JCPS Cluster Spokesperson. Follow us on Twitter: @GCISMedia @GovernmentZA #LocalElections Issued by Government Communication and Information System